		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />CHR-RAM isn't the issue, it's CHR-RAM combined with Mapper 0 (NROM).  Some newer emulators may reject it, probably for the same reason they reject CNROM with more than 32k of CHR-ROM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
